==Chinese==
===Mandarin===
[[Pinyin]]: bù chĭ xià wèn

===Etymology===
*A quote from the [[wikipedia:Analects_of_Confucius|Analects of Confucius]]
#: ''[[子贡]][[问]][[曰]]：“[[孔]][[文]][[子]][[何以]][[谓]][[之]][[文]][[也]]？”[[子曰]]：“[[敏]][[而]][[好]][[学]]，'''不耻下问'''，[[是]][[以]][[谓]][[之]][[文]][[也]]''
#: ''Zigong asked, "How did Kong The Learned come to be (posthumously) dubbed The Learned?"  The Master said, "he was clever and loved to learn, '''he was not ashamed to ask his subordinates''' (if he did not know something).  This is why he was dubbed The Learned."''

===Idiom===
'''[[不]][[耻]][[下]][[问]]'''
# not ashamed to learn from one's subordinates.

===Alternate forms===
[[不恥下問]] ([[Traditional Chinese]])
